   United States Bankruptcy Court
   District of Arizona
     __________________________________________________________________

   Welcome! Today is Wednesday, 01/30/2002. The time is 08:59:40 AM
   Welcome! The Bankruptcy Court for the District of Arizona welcomes you
   to its website. This site will give you information about our
   Electronic Case Filing (ECF) site, allow you to check Local Rules and
   General Orders, download general forms and instructions, browse
   Frequently Asked Questions, find out where to file pleadings, and fill
   out our Guestbook and Survey forms among other items. Please feel free
   to send any suggestions about this site to the Court.
   Bullhead City Cases... All pending BHC cases have been transferred to
   Judge Haines. Click here to see a case listing.
   Important ECF News! We have an important update on Electronic Case
   Filings in the District of Arizona which includes plans for expansion
   to the Yuma and Tucson offices. Click here to read more!
   Visit WebPacer at http://pacer.azb.uscourts.gov. WebPacer is billed at
   $.07
   per page as opposed to the $.60 per minute that PACER/BRASS bills.
   WebPacer provides a single point of access to District of Arizona Cases
   for all offices and uses the same id and password that you currently
   use to access PACER/BRASS. For further information, contact the PACER
   Service Center at 800-676-6856 or call our help line at 602-640-5800
   x647.
   Contact Us! If you experience any problems with or have any questions
   about our site, please contact us by email. Please remember that this
   email is for web related issues and that no pleadings can be filed in
   this way.

